"{\"uid\": \"cyclingnews.com-news-it-could-be-an-uncontrolled-race-mathieu-van-der-poel-ready-for-chaos-at-paris-2024-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  World champion accepts favourite tag but small field makes it unlike a Classic  When you purchase through links on our site, we may earn an affiliate commission.Here's how it works.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 183, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 185, \"to\": 287, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You are now subscribed  Your newsletter sign-up was successful  Mathieu van der Poelbelieves that the potential for chaos in the men's road race at theParis 2024 Olympicscould play to his advantage.\", \"from\": 289, \"to\": 487, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Saturday's race will have a field of just 90 riders, and no single team is likely to be able to control the peloton across its 273km.\", \"from\": 488, \"to\": 621, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"With those small teams, it's a bit of a wait-and-see situation for me, but it does look like it could be an uncontrolled race,\\\" Van der Poel toldWielerflits.\", \"from\": 623, \"to\": 781, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It depends on the legs, but I would say it's an advantage for me.\", \"from\": 782, \"to\": 848, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You have to be on your guard at every moment of the race.\", \"from\": 849, \"to\": 906, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It could happen suddenly, and then you have to make sure you are there.\\\"\", \"from\": 907, \"to\": 979, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Van der Poel will line up as one of the outstanding favourites for the gold medal, alongside Belgium's Remco Evenepoel and Wout van Aert, and home hope Julian Alaphilippe.\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 1152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1084, \"end\": 1099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Remco Evenepoel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Remco_Evenepoel\"}, {\"begin\": 1104, \"end\": 1117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wout van Aert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wout_van_Aert\"}, {\"begin\": 1133, \"end\": 1151, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julian_Alaphilippe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Julian Alaphilippe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julian_Alaphilippe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Julian_Alaphilippe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The role of favourite is not that bad,\\\" Van der Poel said.\", \"from\": 1154, \"to\": 1213, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In a Classic, it is certainly a bit more predictable, because you have your own team with you that can help control the race.\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1340, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's the big difference, but the goal itself remains the same.\\\"\", \"from\": 1341, \"to\": 1406, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Dutchman will hope to replicate hisperformanceat last year's World Championships in Glasgow, when he claimed the rainbow jersey with a devastating long-range attack.\", \"from\": 1408, \"to\": 1577, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1408, \"end\": 1420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Dutchman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Dutchman\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Dutchman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Dutchman\"}, {\"begin\": 1496, \"end\": 1503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\", \"score\": 0.9995153713899254, \"rank\": 0.00048482827403233467, \"text\": \"Glasgow\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\"}, {\"begin\": 1525, \"end\": 1539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rainbow_jersey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"rainbow jersey\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rainbow_jersey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rainbow_jersey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Like last summer, Van der Poel warmed up for the title race by riding the Tour de France primarily in the service of his Alpecin-Deceuninck teammate Jasper Philipsen, helping to tee up a hat-trick of stage wins.\", \"from\": 1578, \"to\": 1789, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1652, \"end\": 1666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9999999404526552, \"rank\": 5.954719187507082e-08, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1727, \"end\": 1743, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jasper_Philipsen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jasper Philipsen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jasper_Philipsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jasper_Philipsen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Van der Poel's own form remains something of a mystery, though he has enjoyed a remarkable season thus far in the rainbow jersey.\", \"from\": 1791, \"to\": 1920, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1905, \"end\": 1919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rainbow_jersey\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"rainbow jersey\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rainbow_jersey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rainbow_jersey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although he raced just seven times before the Tour, Van der Poel collected crushing victories at the Tour of Flanders, Paris-Roubaix and E3 Harelbeke, as well as podium finishes at Gent-Wevelgem and Li\\u00e8ge-Bastogne-Li\\u00e8ge.\", \"from\": 1921, \"to\": 2141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2040, \"end\": 2053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Roubaix\", \"score\": 0.9816675037644488, \"rank\": 0.004431782209560121, \"text\": \"Paris-Roubaix\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Roubaix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Roubaix\"}, {\"begin\": 2058, \"end\": 2070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/E3_Saxo_Bank_Classic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.981761155568727e-13, \"text\": \"E3 Harelbeke\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/E3_Saxo_Bank_Classic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/E3_Saxo_Bank_Classic\"}, {\"begin\": 2102, \"end\": 2115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gent\\u2013Wevelgem\", \"score\": 0.9552661580611375, \"rank\": 0.025687336945615324, \"text\": \"Gent-Wevelgem\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gent\\u2013Wevelgem\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gent\\u2013Wevelgem\"}, {\"begin\": 2120, \"end\": 2140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Li\\u00e8ge\\u2013Bastogne\\u2013Li\\u00e8ge\", \"score\": 0.9746117254733598, \"rank\": 0.016748768472911003, \"text\": \"Li\\u00e8ge-Bastogne-Li\\u00e8ge\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Li\\u00e8ge\\u2013Bastogne\\u2013Li\\u00e8ge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Li\\u00e8ge\\u2013Bastogne\\u2013Li\\u00e8ge\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I came out of the Tour fresher, but that does not mean I will have the legs from the Glasgow World Championships again,\\\" Van der Poel said.\", \"from\": 2143, \"to\": 2283, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Every year is different, of course.\", \"from\": 2284, \"to\": 2320, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have stuck to the preparation I had for Glasgow - not exactly the same, but you still keep it in mind.\\\"\", \"from\": 2321, \"to\": 2426, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2363, \"end\": 2370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\", \"score\": 0.9995153713899254, \"rank\": 0.00048482827403233467, \"text\": \"Glasgow\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 2428, \"to\": 2530, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Van der Poel confirmed that he would forgo the opportunity to reconnoitre the finishing circuit, which is centred on the short, sharp climb up Montmartre.\", \"from\": 2532, \"to\": 2686, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He cited the speed restrictions in place for Thursday's official reconnaissance window, where cyclists had to ride the circuit in a convoy at a maximum speed of 30kph.\", \"from\": 2687, \"to\": 2854, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Van der Poel preferred to train on Thursday in the vicinity of his hotel in Saint-Lambert, southwest of Paris.\", \"from\": 2855, \"to\": 2965, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2931, \"end\": 2944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lasne\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0851416337540645e-23, \"text\": \"Saint-Lambert\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lasne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lasne\"}, {\"begin\": 2959, \"end\": 2964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.565113884006351e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not think it's useful at all.\", \"from\": 2967, \"to\": 3002, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It only makes sense to do it at a higher racing speed,\\\" Van der Poel said of the recon, according toAD.\", \"from\": 3003, \"to\": 3106, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not think it's worth the effort to travel there for an hour and a half.\", \"from\": 3107, \"to\": 3184, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I'd rather choose a training session here and then rest.\", \"from\": 3185, \"to\": 3241, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Of course, I would have preferred to see it myself, but those are considerations.\", \"from\": 3243, \"to\": 3325, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I certainly have a good idea of it.\", \"from\": 3326, \"to\": 3365, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There are a lot of videos, and the national coach gives us all the information.\", \"from\": 3366, \"to\": 3445, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Normally, that climb should suit me well.\", \"from\": 3446, \"to\": 3487, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ambition to win here is very big.\\\"\", \"from\": 3488, \"to\": 3526, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Van der Poel has never previously competed in the road race at the Olympics, having focused on the mountain event in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 3528, \"to\": 3651, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3645, \"end\": 3650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.7049782151165932, \"rank\": 0.41847642567680043, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After crashing out of that event three years ago, Van der Poel had long toyed with the idea of riding both the mountain bike and the road race in Paris.\", \"from\": 3652, \"to\": 3804, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3798, \"end\": 3803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.565113884006351e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He ultimately opted to focus solely on the road race, but he indicated that he might target the mountain bike again in Los Angeles in 2028.\", \"from\": 3805, \"to\": 3944, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3924, \"end\": 3935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999827057667322, \"rank\": 1.7279568058657952e-05, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I actually never ride a mountain bike anymore, unfortunately, not even for fun,\\\" Van der Poel said.\", \"from\": 3946, \"to\": 4046, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The last time was during the test event for the Olympics in September.\", \"from\": 4047, \"to\": 4118, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But yes, I do think about the Olympic Games in Los Angeles in four years' time, and making mountain biking a big goal there.\", \"from\": 4119, \"to\": 4243, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4166, \"end\": 4177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999827057667322, \"rank\": 1.7279568058657952e-05, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By then I will be at the end of my career with another very nice goal.\\\"\", \"from\": 4244, \"to\": 4315, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Get unlimited access to all of our coverage of the 2024 Olympic Games - including breaking news and analysis reported by our journalists on the ground from every event across road, mountain bike, track and BMX racing as it happens and more.Find out more.\", \"from\": 4319, \"to\": 4573, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4525, \"end\": 4535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.6368746636979861, \"rank\": 0.5701676593530625, \"text\": \"BMX racing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barry Ryan was Head of Features at Cyclingnews until 2024.\", \"from\": 4575, \"to\": 4633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4575, \"end\": 4580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Gibb\", \"score\": 0.9403132928065187, \"rank\": 0.06347534123402786, \"text\": \"Barry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Gibb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Gibb\"}, {\"begin\": 4581, \"end\": 4585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"score\": 0.9946219908783664, \"rank\": 0.005405091955236508, \"text\": \"Ryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is currently Editor-in-chief at Domestique.\", \"from\": 4634, \"to\": 4680, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4669, \"end\": 4679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Domestique\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Domestique\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Domestique\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Domestique\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has covered professional cycling since 2010, reporting from the Tour de France, Giro d'Italia and events from Argentina to Japan.\", \"from\": 4681, \"to\": 4813, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4748, \"end\": 4762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9999999404526552, \"rank\": 5.954719187507082e-08, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 4764, \"end\": 4777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\", \"score\": 0.9999989624207881, \"rank\": 1.0375787988763293e-06, \"text\": \"Giro d'Italia\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Giro_d'Italia\"}, {\"begin\": 4794, \"end\": 4803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.7707491757413096, \"rank\": 0.29508397010705395, \"text\": \"Argentina\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Argentina_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4807, \"end\": 4812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.8137761462166746, \"rank\": 0.12588068528136998, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His writing has appeared in The Independent, Procycling and Cycling Plus.\", \"from\": 4814, \"to\": 4887, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He is the author ofThe Ascent: Sean Kelly, Stephen Roche and the Rise of Irish Cycling's Golden Generation, published by Gill Books.\", \"from\": 4888, \"to\": 5020, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4919, \"end\": 4929, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sean_Kelly_Gallery\", \"score\": 0.9999996524453003, \"rank\": 3.045028103762944e-07, \"text\": \"Sean Kelly\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sean_Kelly_Gallery\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sean_Kelly_Gallery\"}, {\"begin\": 4931, \"end\": 4944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Roche\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.1545975702447084e-60, \"text\": \"Stephen Roche\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \